<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-10T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="690" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00 Revolutions/13: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-11T00:00:00-04:00">August 11,
                                1937—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received August 12—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>10. A highly placed person who is reliable and in a position to know,
                            states that a division in the Chaco is in open revolt against central
                            government. This information is strictly confidential and nothing
                            appears to be known outside highest Government circles. City completely
                            tranquil.</p>
                        <p>Many automobiles in front of and much movement at home of President
                            Franco at this moment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>